{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"bpftime","page":{"layout":"document","title":"bpftime-aot","description":"Ahead-of-Time (AOT) compiler for eBPF programs that converts eBPF bytecode to native machine code using LLVM.","bodyHtml":"<p>Ahead-of-Time (AOT) compiler for eBPF programs that converts eBPF bytecode to native machine code using LLVM.</p>\n<h2 id=\"overview\">Overview</h2>\n<p><code>bpftime-aot</code> is a command-line tool that compiles eBPF programs to native ELF objects for high-performance execution in userspace. It supports:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>AOT compilation</strong> from eBPF bytecode to native x86/ARM machine code</li>\n<li><strong>Multiple input sources</strong>: eBPF ELF files or programs in shared memory</li>\n<li><strong>Standalone execution</strong> of compiled programs</li>\n<li><strong>Helper function relocation</strong> for seamless integration</li>\n<li><strong>LLVM IR emission</strong> for debugging and optimization analysis</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For the underlying library, see <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/llvmbpf\">llvmbpf</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"installation\">Installation</h2>\n<p>After building bpftime, the tool is available at:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">~</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">/.bpftime/bpftime-aot</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Or add to PATH</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">export</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> PATH</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$PATH:</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">~</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">/.bpftime/</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"usage\">Usage</h2>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">bpftime-aot [--help] [--version] {build,compile,load,run}</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">Subcommands:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">  build      Build native ELF(s) from eBPF ELF object file</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">  compile    Compile eBPF programs loaded in bpftime shared memory</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">  load       Load a compiled native ELF into shared memory</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">  run        Execute a compiled native ELF program</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"command-reference\">Command Reference</h2>\n<h3 id=\"build---compile-from-ebpf-elf\">build - Compile from eBPF ELF</h3>\n<p>Compile eBPF programs from an ELF object file to native code:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> &#x3C;</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">EBPF_EL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">F</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">></span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> [-o </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">OUTPUT_DIR]</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> [-e]</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">Options:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">  -o,</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --output</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> DIR</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">    Output</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> directory</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> (default: </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">current</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> directory</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">  -e,</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> --emit_llvm</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">     Emit</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> LLVM</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> IR</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> instead</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> of</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> native</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> object</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> code</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Compile all programs in an eBPF ELF</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> example/uprobe.bpf.o</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -o</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> output/</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Generate LLVM IR for analysis</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> example/uprobe.bpf.o</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -e</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>Each eBPF program in the ELF will produce a separate <code>.o</code> file (e.g., <code>do_uprobe.o</code>).</p>\n<h3 id=\"compile---compile-from-shared-memory\">compile - Compile from Shared Memory</h3>\n<p>Compile eBPF programs already loaded in bpftime shared memory:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> compile</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> [-o </span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">OUTPUT_DIR]</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> [-e]</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p><strong>Example - Full workflow:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Load eBPF programs into shared memory:</li>\n</ol>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">LD_PRELOAD</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">build/runtime/syscall-server/libbpftime-syscall-server.so</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> example/malloc/malloc</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>Compile the loaded program to native code:</li>\n</ol>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> compile</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>Output: <code>do_count.o</code> (native ELF object)</p>\n<p><strong>Key advantage:</strong> When compiling from shared memory, maps, global variables, and helper functions are already relocated, making the compiled code ready for integration.</p>\n<h3 id=\"load---load-compiled-elf-to-shared-memory\">load - Load Compiled ELF to Shared Memory</h3>\n<p>Load a pre-compiled native ELF into shared memory for execution:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> load</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> &#x3C;</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">PAT</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">H</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">></span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> &#x3C;</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">I</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">D</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">></span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">Arguments:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">  PATH</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">    Path</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> to</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> the</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> compiled</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> native</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ELF</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> file</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">  ID</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">      Program</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ID</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> in</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> shared</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> memory</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> to</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> update</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Load compiled native code for program ID 4</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> load</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> do_count.o</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 4</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h3 id=\"run---execute-compiled-program\">run - Execute Compiled Program</h3>\n<p>Run a compiled native ELF program directly:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> &#x3C;</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">PAT</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">H</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">></span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> [MEMORY]</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">Arguments:</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">  PATH</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">      Path</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> to</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> the</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> compiled</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> native</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ELF</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">  MEMORY</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">    Optional:</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> Path</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> to</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> memory</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> file</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> for</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> program</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> context</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Run compiled program</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> do_uprobe_trace.o</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># Run with memory context</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> program.o</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> memory.bin</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"integration-examples\">Integration Examples</h2>\n<h3 id=\"linking-with-custom-programs\">Linking with Custom Programs</h3>\n<p>You can link compiled eBPF programs with your C/C++ applications:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">cd</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> tools/aot/example</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">clang</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -O2</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> main.c</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> do_count.o</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -o</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> malloc</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">./malloc</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>The driver program needs to implement required helper functions:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"c\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"c\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#include</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> &#x3C;stdio.h></span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#include</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> &#x3C;stdint.h></span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#include</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> &#x3C;unistd.h></span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">#include</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> &#x3C;stdarg.h></span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">// Entry point - called from main</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">int</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> bpf_main</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">void*</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> ctx</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> size</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">// Helper function implementations</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> _bpf_helper_ext_0006</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> fmt</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> fmt_size</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, ...) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">    // bpf_printk implementation</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    va_list args;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    va_start</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(args, fmt);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    vprintf</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">((</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> char</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)fmt, args);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    va_end</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(args);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> _bpf_helper_ext_0014</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">void</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">    // bpf_get_current_pid_tgid implementation</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> ((</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">getpid</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">() </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">&#x3C;&#x3C;</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 32</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">|</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> gettid</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">();</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\">// Map operations (simplified mock)</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> counter </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">void</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">_bpf_helper_ext_0001</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">void</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">map</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> void</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">key</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> &#x26;</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">counter;</span><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // bpf_map_lookup_elem</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">long</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> _bpf_helper_ext_0002</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">void</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">map</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> void</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">key</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">,</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">                          const</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> void</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">value</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> flags</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">    counter </span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> *</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t*</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">)value;</span><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // bpf_map_update_elem</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint64_t</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> __lddw_helper_map_by_fd</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\">uint32_t</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> id</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">) {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span><span style=\"color:#768390\">  // Map relocation helper</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">int</span><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\"> main</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">() {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#DCBDFB\">    bpf_main</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">(</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">NULL</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">);</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    return</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> 0</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">}</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h3 id=\"helper-function-naming-convention\">Helper Function Naming Convention</h3>\n<p>Helper functions are named <code>_bpf_helper_ext_XXXX</code> where <code>XXXX</code> is the helper ID:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>0001</code> = bpf_map_lookup_elem</li>\n<li><code>0002</code> = bpf_map_update_elem</li>\n<li><code>0006</code> = bpf_printk</li>\n<li><code>0014</code> = bpf_get_current_pid_tgid</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"understanding-relocation\">Understanding Relocation</h3>\n<p>When compiling from shared memory (using <code>bpftime-aot compile</code>):</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Maps are relocated</strong>: <code>__lddw_helper_map_by_fd</code> receives actual shared memory map IDs</li>\n<li><strong>Helpers are resolved</strong>: Helper function addresses are fixed up</li>\n<li><strong>Global variables are linked</strong>: Accessible through shared memory</li>\n</ul>\n<p>See <code>tools/aot/example/</code> for complete working examples.</p>\n<h2 id=\"advanced-usage\">Advanced Usage</h2>\n<h3 id=\"emitting-llvm-ir\">Emitting LLVM IR</h3>\n<p>Generate LLVM IR for optimization analysis or debugging:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># From eBPF ELF</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> build</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> uprobe.bpf.o</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -e</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"> </span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#768390\"># From shared memory</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">bpftime-aot</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> compile</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -e</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>Output files will have <code>.ll</code> extension containing human-readable LLVM IR.</p>\n<h3 id=\"example-output\">Example Output</h3>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"shellsession\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">$ bpftime-aot run do_uprobe_trace.o</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">[info] [llvm_jit_context.cpp:81] Initializing llvm</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">[info] [llvm_jit_context.cpp:204] LLVM-JIT: Loading aot object</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">target_func called.</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\">[info] [main.cpp:190] Output: 0</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"performance-benefits\">Performance Benefits</h2>\n<p>AOT compilation provides significant performance advantages:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>No JIT overhead</strong>: Compilation happens once, offline</li>\n<li><strong>Optimized native code</strong>: Full LLVM optimization pipeline</li>\n<li><strong>Reduced startup time</strong>: Programs start immediately</li>\n<li><strong>Better code placement</strong>: Improved instruction cache utilization</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Typical speedup: 2-5x faster than JIT, 10-50x faster than interpreter.</p>\n<h2 id=\"troubleshooting\">Troubleshooting</h2>\n<p><strong>Q: \"Unable to open BPF elf\" error</strong>\nA: Ensure the eBPF ELF file is compiled with clang and contains valid BTF information.</p>\n<p><strong>Q: \"Invalid id not exist\" when loading</strong>\nA: Verify the program ID exists in shared memory using <code>bpftimetool export</code>.</p>\n<p><strong>Q: Helper function undefined</strong>\nA: Implement all required <code>_bpf_helper_ext_XXXX</code> functions in your driver program.</p>\n<h2 id=\"see-also\">See Also</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/bpftime/tree/master/tools/bpftimetool\">bpftimetool</a> - Shared memory inspection tool</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/bpftime/blob/master/tools/aot/optimize.md\">optimize.md</a> - Optimization guide</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/llvmbpf\">llvmbpf</a> - Underlying LLVM library</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/bpftime\">bpftime documentation</a> - Main project documentation</li>\n</ul>","headings":[{"id":"overview","text":"Overview","depth":2},{"id":"installation","text":"Installation","depth":2},{"id":"usage","text":"Usage","depth":2},{"id":"command-reference","text":"Command Reference","depth":2},{"id":"build---compile-from-ebpf-elf","text":"build - Compile from eBPF ELF","depth":3},{"id":"compile---compile-from-shared-memory","text":"compile - Compile from Shared Memory","depth":3},{"id":"load---load-compiled-elf-to-shared-memory","text":"load - Load Compiled ELF to Shared Memory","depth":3},{"id":"run---execute-compiled-program","text":"run - Execute Compiled Program","depth":3},{"id":"integration-examples","text":"Integration Examples","depth":2},{"id":"linking-with-custom-programs","text":"Linking with Custom Programs","depth":3},{"id":"helper-function-naming-convention","text":"Helper Function Naming Convention","depth":3},{"id":"understanding-relocation","text":"Understanding Relocation","depth":3},{"id":"advanced-usage","text":"Advanced Usage","depth":2},{"id":"emitting-llvm-ir","text":"Emitting LLVM IR","depth":3},{"id":"example-output","text":"Example Output","depth":3},{"id":"performance-benefits","text":"Performance Benefits","depth":2},{"id":"troubleshooting","text":"Troubleshooting","depth":2},{"id":"see-also","text":"See Also","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/bpftime/documents/bpftimeaot.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2025-09-30T07:42:21.000Z","createdAt":"2024-08-11T10:36:47.000Z","authors":[{"name":"yunwei37","email":"yunwei356@gmail.com"}]},"path":"/zh/bpftime/documents/bpftimeaot/","alternates":{"en":"/bpftime/documents/bpftimeaot/","zh":"/zh/bpftime/documents/bpftimeaot/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"bpftime","description":"High-performance userspace eBPF runtime and extension framework for production tracing, runtime extension, and low-overhead instrumentation.","href":"/zh/bpftime/"},"previous":{"title":"bpftimetool","description":"Command-line tool for inspecting and managing bpftime shared memory state.","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/bpftimetool/"},"next":{"title":"Contact and citations","description":"Have any questions or suggestions on future development? Free free to open an issue or contact <mailto:yunwei356@gmail.com and <team@eunomia.dev!","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/contact/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"bpftime","items":[{"title":"bpftime","href":"/zh/bpftime/","depth":0},{"title":"简介","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/introduction/","depth":2},{"title":"Installation and Test","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/build-and-test/","depth":2},{"title":"Manual","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"Examples & Use Cases","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/examples/","depth":2},{"title":"Available kernel features in userspace","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/available-features/","depth":2},{"title":"Write and Run eBPF on GPU with bpftime","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/gpu/","depth":2},{"title":"The design and implementation of bpftime","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/how-it-works/","depth":2},{"title":"Benchmark and performance evaluation for bpftime","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/performance/","depth":2},{"title":"Compile Once, Run Everywhere(CO-RE)","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/co-re/","depth":2},{"title":"bpftime Attach System","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/attach/","depth":2},{"title":"bpftimetool","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/bpftimetool/","depth":2},{"title":"bpftime-aot","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/bpftimeaot/","depth":2},{"title":"Contact and citations","href":"/zh/bpftime/documents/contact/","depth":2},{"title":"Userspace eBPF VM with LLVM JIT/AOT Compiler","href":"/zh/bpftime/llvmbpf/","depth":1},{"title":"EIM: Extension Interface Model","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/","depth":1},{"title":"EIM: Extension Interface Model Specification","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/spec/","depth":2},{"title":"UProbe Role Definition README","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/uprobe/","depth":2},{"title":"EIM: Example code","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/example/","depth":2},{"title":"EIM Usage and people involved (Draft v1)","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"studies on bugs in extensions/plugins","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/study/","depth":2},{"title":"关于浏览器扩展和 IDE 插件漏洞的研究","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/study/browser-ide-bug-study/","depth":3},{"title":"关于数据库和 Web 服务器扩展接口中的缺陷研究","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/study/db-bug-study/","depth":3},{"title":"关于虚拟机管理程序和容器扩展漏洞的研究（2018–2024）","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/study/docker-vm-bug-study/","depth":3},{"title":"关于生产力软件和游戏扩展/插件漏洞的案例研究（2018–2024）","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/study/game-office-bug-study/","depth":3},{"title":"Extension Systems compare with EIM","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/study/compare/","depth":3},{"title":"EIM on verify: what can it do and what cannot","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/draft-spec/current-EIM-lack/","depth":3},{"title":"spec_core","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/draft-spec/spec_core/","depth":3},{"title":"Extension Model Specification V1","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/draft-spec/spec_old/","depth":3},{"title":"Extension Inferface Model Specification V3","href":"/zh/bpftime/EIM/draft-spec/spec/","depth":3}]}]}},"__N_SSG":true}